UNITED STATES FIDELITY & GUARANTY CO. v. BLAKE. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. February 5, 1923. Rehearing Denied February 19, 1923.) No. 3891. Jos. A. McCullough, of Baltimore, Md., and Chadwick, McMicken, Ramsey & Rupp, of Seattle, Wash., for plaintiff in error. Richard H. Johnson and Carey H. Nixon, both of Boise, Idaho, for defendant in error.

Before GILBERT and HUNT, Circuit Judges, and WOLVERTON, District Judge.

GILBERT, Circuit Judge.

By stipulation of the parties hereto, decision in this ease was to conform to the decision rendered in case 3890, United States Fidelity & Guaranty Co. v. Robert S. Blake, 285 Fed. 449. The judgment of the court below is accordingly hereby affirmed.
